word_mean_info__list.difference: 书面用词，指对将要或预料要发生的事怍于期待状态。
指对未来的期望，一般是对好事的期待。
指希望得到积极、有利的结果，所期待的可能实现，也可能不会实现。

bilingual.source: I anticipate a positive outcome from the meeting.
bilingual.target: 我预期会议会有一个积极的结果。

bilingual.source: We anticipate heavy traffic during the holiday season.
bilingual.target: 我们预期假期期间会有严重的交通堵塞。

bilingual.source: Yes, we do not anticipate any changes.
bilingual.target: 是的，我们并不预期的任何变化。

bilingual.source: What changes do you anticipate in the industry?
bilingual.target: 这一行业您预期会有甚麽改变?。

bilingual.source: Don't pick a day when you anticipate being under stress.
bilingual.target: 千万不要选择一个预期充满压力的日子戒烟。

bilingual.source: Every attempt should be made to anticipate this generation gap.
bilingual.target: 应该千方百计地预期到会产生这样的代沟.

bilingual.source: Anticipate doing sth. = expect to do sth. We anticipate shipping the goods next week. = We expect to ship the goods next week.
bilingual.target: 我们期望下周装货anticipate一般指预期可喜的事，而expect则不一一般指预期可喜的事，定。

bilingual.source: They anticipate moving to bigger premises by the end of the year.
bilingual.target: 他们预期年底前迁入较大的经营场所。

list.abstract: anticipate（英[ænˈtɪsɪpeɪt]，美[ænˈtɪsɪpeɪt]），英语单词。作动词用，认为…很有可能；期望；预料；先于…行动；盼望；为…早做准备；在… 之前来到等。英语短句有anticipate growth，译为预期增长，例句为：They anticipate other people's suspicious reactions.（他们预判其他人的可疑反应。） 第三人称单数：anticipates，现在分词：anticipating，过去式：anticipated，过去分词：anticipated
《Anticipate》是Ani Difranco演唱的英文歌曲，收录于1993年10月1日发行的专辑《Like I Said》中。

yingyinNormal.en: When we fart we know it, and can anticipate the accompanying smell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们知道我们自己放屁，也会预期有什么样的味道。

yingyinNormal.en: I know. Every Saturday at 8:15. Easy to anticipate.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我知道每个周六的8点15分，老少咸宜。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, we always anticipate a certain level of graft.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们早预计会遇到一定程度的腐败。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, then I anticipate an awkward situation when you get home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那我预测你回家会面临个尴尬的境地。

yingyinNormal.en: Could you back up a bit? We anticipate a suit against this jurisdiction.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们能退后一点吗？我们会起诉该司法机关。

yingyinNormal.en: How much domestic workforce would you anticipate shedding as a result of this merger?
yingyinNormal.zh: 由于这次兼并，你预计将辞退多少国内员工？

yingyinNormal.en: We hit a few speed bumps early on. It began to anticipate where the food would come from.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们前段时间出了点小问题，它开始预见食物出现的方向。

yingyinNormal.en: You have a statement? You anticipate any other big WikiLeaks info dumps coming down the pike?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你写好声明了吗？还会不会有其他重大的维基解密事件？

yingyinNormal.en: And what do you do when something goes wrong? You want to anticipate it. It's starting to snow.
yingyinNormal.zh: 出岔子了你会怎么办？事先要有所预料到，不然会越滚越大的。
